<paragraph blockId="6.[189,310,1647,1673]" box="[189,310,1647,1673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1647,1673]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1647,1673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,1694,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">This new species differs from all other Middle East congeners in having the following combination of characters: thorax orange-brown with distinctly paler scutellum; legs uniformly brownish; fore femur with 6–9 ventral spines; male gonostylus long, with pointed apex; parameres long, slender, slightly curved dorsally; female with 2 subspherical seminal capsules with very long necks.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
