<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,334,685,711]" box="[189,334,685,711]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,685,711]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,685,711]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,732,899]" box="[234,298,732,758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,732,758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,732,899]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
HEAD. Uniformly pale brown. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[696,794,767,794]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Bezzia sharjahi Szadziewski &amp; Alwin sp. nov. A. Wing, ♀. B. Antennal flagellum, ♂. C. Antennal flagellum, ♀. D. Genitalia, ♂. E. Parameres. F. Aedeagus. G. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827455/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) pale brown; flagellar plume poorly developed; flagellomeres 2(3)–13 with paler basal halves; flagellomeres 10–13 short; total flagellum length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.50– 0.70 mm</quantity>
; antennal ratio 0.50–0.70. Palpus yellow, slender; third palpal segment short, with distinct capitate sensilla; palpal ratio 2.00.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,938,1070]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
THORAX. Orange-brown; scutellum paler. Wing pale, with barely visible veins; 1 poorly marked long radial cell; wing length 
<quantity box="[466,640,974,1000]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.1" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.9">0.90–1.30 mm</quantity>
; costal ratio 0.70–0.80. Legs uniformly pale brown, tarsi slightly paler, coxae dark brown; claws small and equal on all legs; fore femur armed with 4–8 short ventral spines; tarsal ratio of fore leg 1.60–1.90, of mid leg 1.80–2.30, of hind leg 2.10–2.20.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,490,1109,1136]" box="[189,490,1109,1136]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">ABDOMEN. Orange brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1175,1307]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
GENITALIA (
<figureCitation box="[323,396,1175,1201]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Bezzia sharjahi Szadziewski &amp; Alwin sp. nov. A. Wing, ♀. B. Antennal flagellum, ♂. C. Antennal flagellum, ♀. D. Genitalia, ♂. E. Parameres. F. Aedeagus. G. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827455/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D–F). Tergite IX short, reaching apex of gonocoxite; sternite IX short. Gonocoxite short, stout; gonostylus long, narrow, distal half curved, with sharp apex. Parameres (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1309,1210,1236]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Bezzia sharjahi Szadziewski &amp; Alwin sp. nov. A. Wing, ♀. B. Antennal flagellum, ♂. C. Antennal flagellum, ♀. D. Genitalia, ♂. E. Parameres. F. Aedeagus. G. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827455/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) fused, tongue-like, slightly curved dorsally, with blunt apex. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[946,1032,1245,1271]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Bezzia sharjahi Szadziewski &amp; Alwin sp. nov. A. Wing, ♀. B. Antennal flagellum, ♂. C. Antennal flagellum, ♀. D. Genitalia, ♂. E. Parameres. F. Aedeagus. G. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827455/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
) triangular, with low basal arch and barely visible rounded apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1346,1513]" box="[234,325,1346,1372]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,1346,1372]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1346,1513]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
HEAD. Brown. Antennal flagellum (
<figureCitation box="[601,691,1381,1407]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Bezzia sharjahi Szadziewski &amp; Alwin sp. nov. A. Wing, ♀. B. Antennal flagellum, ♂. C. Antennal flagellum, ♀. D. Genitalia, ♂. E. Parameres. F. Aedeagus. G. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827455/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) with short flagellomeres, brown, proximal portions yellow; total flagellum length 
<quantity box="[460,638,1416,1443]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.50–0.70 mm</quantity>
; antennal ratio 0.80–1.10. Palpus slender, yellow; third palpal segment short, rather stout, without sensory pit; palpal ratio 2.00–2.50. Mandible with 6–8 massive distal teeth and numerous smaller proximal teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,1552,1720]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
THORAX. Orange brown; scutellum paler. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[758,852,1552,1578]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[233,1354,263,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Bezzia sharjahi Szadziewski &amp; Alwin sp. nov. A. Wing, ♀. B. Antennal flagellum, ♂. C. Antennal flagellum, ♀. D. Genitalia, ♂. E. Parameres. F. Aedeagus. G. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827455/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) venation similar to that of male; wing length 
